JavaScript typing workflow (no `.ts` source files):

- Keep implementation files as `.js` only.
- Add `// @ts-check` at the top of every new or modified `.js` source file.
- For each function or construct, document argument and return types with JSDoc (`@param`, `@returns`, and `@typedef` where needed).
- Prefer shared JSDoc typedefs for domain objects instead of repeating inline object shapes.
- Keep `public/tsconfig.json` configured for JS type checking (`allowJs: true`, `checkJs: true`, `noEmit: true`).
- Run `npm run typecheck` in `public/` after changes and fix any new type diagnostics.
